Migrate Data Cloud Permission Sets using User Access Policies

Learn how to use user access policies to grant updated Data Cloud permission sets to groups of users based on criteria you set.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To modify user access policies:	Manage User Access Policies
NOTE The Data Cloud Admin and Data Cloud Marketing Admin standard permission sets are compatible with both legacy or enhanced security data spaces because they permit admins to view features and feature setup across all data spaces. However, you must associate data spaces with the admin permission sets to give admins access to data within the data spaces.
Create a user access policy.
Set the Trigger Type to None so that the policy is run manually.
Set the criteria filter to select all users with the permission set you will replace. You must identify both the users’ Data Cloud permission sets and the data space permission set.
Select the Grant action, and apply the action to the permission sets.
If you have more than 1,000 users, change the Status to Migrate before applying the user access policy
After enabling enhanced security data spaces, set up user access policies to remove your users from legacy permission sets.
EXAMPLE

Suppose you’re migrating users who are Data Cloud marketing managers who have access to the legacy Southwest Region data space permission set.

First, prepare your org by cloning the new Data Cloud Marketing Manager standard permission set to a custom permission set named, for example, Data Cloud Marketing Managers--SW Region. Associate the new permission set with the Southwest Region data space. Set feature access for the data space as needed.

Next, create a user access policy and set the filter criteria to select users with these legacy permission sets:

(Legacy) Data Cloud Marketing Manager permission set
Southwest Region data space permission set

Next, select the Grant action, and grant this permission set:

Data Cloud Marketing Managers--SW Region permission set

Grant the new permission set to the selected users by clicking Apply.

After enabling enhanced security data spaces, create a new user access policy to remove the old permission sets from your migrated users.

Set the filter criteria to users with this permission set:

Data Cloud Marketing Managers--SW Region permission set

Select the Revoke action, and remove these permission sets:

(Legacy) Data Cloud Marketing Manager permission set
Southwest Region data space permission set

Revoke the old permission sets from the selected users by clicking Apply.
